    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and grate (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based,<strong> hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a matching lid over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>giant couscous</strong>, <strong>chicken stock mix</strong>, <strong>remaining ground turmeric</strong>, <strong>spinach</strong>, <strong>grated garlic</strong>, a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and 400ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[600ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[800ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up</p>",
